Section 4 -- Transfer and Exceptions to Public Use Restrictions.

a. General Rule on Public Use. You may not use the Licensed Material in public environments involving more than ten (10) individuals unless explicitly authorized by the Licensor under the terms of a separate contract, as outlined in this Section.

b. Contract for Exceptions. The Licensor may, at its sole discretion, allow exceptions to the public use limitations through a written contract that may or may not involve financial compensation. All contracts must be detailed in a file named KEYLICENSE.md, specifying the user, the duration, and the scope of the granted exceptions.

c. License Types. The contract may establish the following types of access:

sql

   1. **Temporary Access.** The user is granted temporary access to the Licensed Material for a set period of time, which cannot be revoked by the Licensor until the expiration of the term.

   2. **Revocable Temporary Access.** The user is granted temporary access, but the Licensor may revoke access at any time.

   3. **Revocable Permanent Access.** The user is granted permanent access, but the Licensor may revoke access at any time.

d. Languages of Contract. Any contractual agreements or exceptions must be documented in English, Russian, and Spanish.

e. Duration. Each exception must include a start date and an expiration date.
Section 5 -- Repository Storage Requirements.

a. The OANCLPU License and Licensed Material must be stored together in the same repository when hosted on platforms such as GitHub. This includes ensuring that the KEYLICENSE.md file is present in the same repository.
